defs.name: BoolTrie
defs.value: BoolTrie { r1, r2, r3, r4, r5, r6 }
defs.docs:
BoolTrie is a trie for representing a set of Unicode codepoints. It is
 implemented with postfix compression (sharing of identical child nodes),
 which gives both compact size and fast lookup.

defs.name: UNICODE_VERSION
defs.docs:
The version of [Unicode](http://www.unicode.org/) that the Unicode parts of
 `CharExt` and `UnicodeStrPrelude` traits are based on.

defs.name: SplitWhitespace
defs.docs:
An iterator over the non-whitespace substrings of a string,
 separated by any amount of whitespace.

defs.name: Utf16Encoder
defs.docs: Iterator adaptor for encoding `char`s to UTF-16.

defs.name: ToLowercase
defs.docs: Returns an iterator that yields the lowercase equivalent of a `char`.

defs.name: ToUppercase
defs.docs: Returns an iterator that yields the uppercase equivalent of a `char`.

defs.name: DecodeUtf16
defs.docs: An iterator that decodes UTF-16 encoded code points from an iterator of `u16`s.

defs.name: DecodeUtf16Error
defs.docs: An error that can be returned when decoding UTF-16 code points.

defs.name: decode_utf16
defs.docs:
Create an iterator over the UTF-16 encoded code points in `iter`,
 returning unpaired surrogates as `Err`s.

defs.name: REPLACEMENT_CHARACTER
defs.docs:
`U+FFFD REPLACEMENT CHARACTER` () is used in Unicode to represent a
 decoding error.

defs.name: valid
defs.docs:
Sequence of valid chars.
 Can be empty between broken UTF-8 chars.

defs.name: broken
defs.docs:
Single broken char, empty if none.
 Empty iff iterator item is last.
